   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COFED CBCA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a co-funded project CAID and European Fund for Development (EFD/FED) to support the commission  (CDJP) work on Governance issues in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). It&#x2019;s a 4 years project starting from October 2015 &#x2013; October 2019). it is focused on promoting strategies for effective involvement of Civil Society Organisations (CSOs) for the Congolese people. This project aims to consolidate good governance mechanisms through greater involvement of CSOs from the grassroots level at national level in the management of public affairs. The project&apos;s overall objective is to promote appropriate strategies for an effective intervention of CSOs in favour of improving living conditions of the Congolese people specifically in 12 provinces of the DRC namely , Tshopo, North Kivu, South Kivu, Tanganyika, Haut Katanga, Lualaba, Kasai Oriental, Kasai Central,  Kwilu, Central Kongo, Kinshasa, Equateur, But CDJP BOMA is work specially in  Central Congo
This project will be implemented by a consortium of Churches Roman Catholic, Anglican, CBCA . And the churd CBCA  will cover the city of Goma, Bukavu and Kinsangani</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will give voice to local communities to be heard at different decision-making levels through advocacy actions to be undertaken. So a strong interaction will be developed between the local population and their authorities and will reinforce the partnership between Non State Actors (NSAs) and authorities at the top as well as donors in terms of developing policies for Provinces in DRC.
-	This project will consolidate local structures and local mechanisms for dialogue as well as the monitoring of policies to improve the well-being of the Congolese people.
-	This project will contribute to the development of the DRC, in particular through the integration of gender issues, environmental as well as accountability, etc. to promote good governance at all decision-making levels.</narrative>
  </description>
